---
import "../styles/global.css";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import Navbar from "../components/Navbar.astro";
---

<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <meta charset="utf-8" />
        <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/icon.svg" />
        <link rel="alternate icon" type="image/png" sizes="48x48" href="/icon48.png" />
        <link rel="alternate icon" type="image/png" sizes="16x16" href="/icon16.png" />
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
        <meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
        <title>Terms and Conditions | Sharp Tabs</title>
        <meta
            name="description"
            content="Friendly Terms and Conditions for Sharp Tabs Chrome Extension, a simple indie project."
        />

    </head>
    <body class="min-h-screen bg-[#03060f] transition-colors duration-300">
        <Navbar />
        <main class="mx-auto mt-24 max-w-3xl px-4 py-12 text-white/80">
            <h1 class="mb-6 text-3xl font-bold">Terms and Conditions</h1>
            <p class="mb-4 text-sm text-gray-500">Last updated: June 6th, 2025</p>
            <section class="mb-8">
                <h2 class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold">Welcome!</h2>
                <p>
                    Thanks for checking out Sharp Tabs! This is a Chrome extension made by a solo developer to help you
                    manage your tabs more easily. These terms are here to keep things clear and friendly.
                </p>
            </section>
            <section class="mb-8">
                <h2 class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold">1. Using Sharp Tabs</h2>
                <p>
                    By using Sharp Tabs, you agree to these simple terms. If you have any questions or suggestions, feel
                    free to reach out at <a
                        href="mailto:support@sharptabs.com"
                        class="text-blue-400 underline">support@sharptabs.com</a
                    >.
                </p>
            </section>
            <section class="mb-8">
                <h2 class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold">2. What Sharp Tabs Does</h2>
                <p>
                    Sharp Tabs is a Chrome extension for better tab management, including vertical tabs and some
                    customization. Some features are free, and a few are part of a small premium plan to help cover
                    development costs.
                </p>
            </section>
            <section class="mb-8">
                <h2 class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold">3. Premium Plan</h2>
                <p>
                    If you choose to support Sharp Tabs by subscribing to the premium plan, thank you! Premium helps
                    keep the project going. You can cancel anytime, and if you have any issues, just let me know and
                    I'll do my best to help.
                </p>
            </section>
            <section class="mb-8">
                <h2 class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold">4. Respectful Use</h2>
                <p>
                    Please use Sharp Tabs as intended and don't try to break it, crack it, or create clones based on
                    it's code without permission.
                </p>
            </section>
            <section class="mb-8">
                <h2 class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold">5. Privacy</h2>
                <p>
                    Your privacy matters. Sharp Tabs doesn't collect any personal or sensitive data at all . We only
                    store your email address if you create an account. We also store details about your Sharp Tabs
                    account (registration date, email verification status, subscription details), you're free to use
                    Sharp Tabs without an account.
                    <br />
                    We only optionally Anonymously track the non-sensitive applied settings (once per day max when you close
                    the settings page), this is to get stats about which settings are most used, and help guide development.
                    You can easily toggle this off at any time in the general settings section at the top of the settings
                    page.
                    <br />
                    Please check out the <a href="/privacy-policy" class="text-blue-400 underline"
                        >Privacy Policy</a
                    > for more details.
                </p>
            </section>
            <section class="mb-8">
                <h2 class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold">6. No Guarantees</h2>
                <p>
                    I do my best to keep Sharp Tabs working well, but sometimes things might break or not work as
                    expected. If you run into issues, please let me know and I'll try to fix them!
                </p>
            </section>
            <section class="mb-8">
                <h2 class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold">7. Changes to These Terms</h2>
                <p>
                    If these terms change, I'll update this page. By continuing to use Sharp Tabs, you're agreeing to
                    the latest version of the terms. I will add a message on the app's settings when this is done.
                </p>
            </section>
            <section class="mb-8">
                <h2 class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold">8. Contact</h2>
                <p>
                    Questions, feedback, or just want to say hi? Email me at support@sharptabs.com. I'd love to hear
                    from you!
                </p>
            </section>
        </main>
        <Footer />
    </body>
</html>
